  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);&quot;&gt;The proposed front lightwell would be at odds with the pattern of development in the area and would introduce an incongruous and discordant feature into the street scene to the detriment of the host building, wider&amp;nbsp; terrace of which it forms part and would fail to preserve or enhance the character of the Graham Road and Mapledene Conservation Area. As such the proposal is contrary to&amp;nbsp; policy D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245);&quot;&gt;of the London Plan (2021); policy LP1 (Design quality and local character) and LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
